In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims April 3, 2012, as Education and Sharing Day, U.S.A. The proclamation highlights the importance of education and character development in American society. The President emphasizes the need to equip children with the necessary tools for success in a global economy that demands higher education and advanced training. He acknowledges the role of parents, caregivers, teachers, and mentors in guiding children towards achievement. Additionally, President Obama recognizes that formal education alone cannot secure the promise of tomorrow and emphasizes the importance of compassion, cooperation, and goodwill towards others. He reflects on the teachings of Rabbi Menachem Mendel Schneerson, who advocated for youth education and inspired millions to practice kindness and generosity. The President calls upon all Americans to observe Education and Sharing Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.